          <p>
            I am a Ph.D. student at the <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" href="https://lsa.umich.edu/astro">University of Michigan Department of Astronomy</a>, where I work with Prof. <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" href="http://www-personal.umich.edu/~ognedin/">Oleg Gnedin</a>. Before coming to Michigan, I received my B.S. degree at <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" href="http://www.phy.pku.edu.cn/">Peking University School of Physics</a> in Jul. 2020. My current research focuses on the formation and evolution of star clusters in cosmological context. <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" href="research.html">Click here</a> to view my research in detail.
